        <mxCell id="xCRE8wccOKQfFn8-C-6z-194" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=1;strokeColor=none;strokeWidth=0.5;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center; margin-top: 0px; line-height: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px; line-height: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px; line-height: 100%;&quot; face=&quot;Helvetica&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;DATA TYPES&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px; box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px; box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Inter, sans-serif; box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Quantitative variables&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;represent amounts of things (e.g. the number of trees in a forest).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-weight: 400; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Types of quantitative variables include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px; box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Continuous&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px;&quot;&gt;: represent measures and can usually be divided into units smaller than one (e.g. 0.75 grams).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px;&quot;&gt;Discrete&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px;&quot;&gt;: represent counts and usually can’t be divided into units smaller than one (e.g. 1 tree).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent; font-size: 9px; font-family: Inter, sans-serif; box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder; line-height: 9px;&quot;&gt;Categorical variables&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent; font-size: 9px; font-family: Inter, sans-serif; line-height: 9px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;represent groupings of things (e.g. the different tree species in a forest). Types of categorical variables include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px;&quot;&gt;Ordinal&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px;&quot;&gt;: represent data with an order (e.g. rankings).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px;&quot;&gt;Nominal&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px;&quot;&gt;: represent group names (e.g. brands or species names).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px; box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Binary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 9px;&quot;&gt;: represent data with a yes/no or 1/0 outcome (e.g. win or lose).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote style=&quot;margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-family: Inter, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="330" x="20" y="480" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
