        <mxCell id="7nWFPXopERBmQTWbtrVL-206" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;rotation=0;" value="&lt;font style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Parametric&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 9px;&quot;&gt;Normally Distributed&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="262.5" x="663.75" y="576" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="7nWFPXopERBmQTWbtrVL-207" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;rotation=0;" value="&lt;font style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Non-Parametric&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="262.5" x="640" y="1136" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="-j6op6PoYftNq8PSPCjF-1" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=1;strokeColor=none;strokeWidth=0.5;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center; margin-top: 0px; line-height: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;&quot;&gt;WHEN TO GO NON-PARAMETRIC&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); box-sizing: inherit;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;1. The &quot;Small &amp;amp; Ugly&quot; Rule&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Condition:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;N&amp;lt;30 AND Data is Skewed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;2. &quot;The Billionaire Steps in&quot; Rule&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Condition: Massive outliers exist (regardless of sample size).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;If you care about the typical case (median) rather than the total sum (mean), use Non-Parametric.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;3. Ranks: The &quot;Star Rating&quot; Rule&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;To calculate a Mean, you assume the distance between 1 and 2 is exactly the same as the distance between 4 and 5. The Reality: Psychology says otherwise. The emotional gap between 1 and 2 is often massive, while the gap between 4 and 5 is small. Averaging them flattens this nuance.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;blockquote style=&quot;margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-family: Inter, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="234" width="340" x="20" y="910" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
